<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8523" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στεφάνη</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στέφω</span>): that which surrounds, encircles anything at the
          top, as if it were a <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">crown.</span> Hence (1) a woman's
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">head-band</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            18.597</span></i>. (See cuts Nos. 16, 40, 41.)—(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">brim</span>
          or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">visor</span> of a helmet, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">helmet</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.96</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            10.30</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.12</span></i>. (See cuts
          Nos. 12, 79, 80, 81, 86, 116.)—(3) of the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">edge</span> of a
          cliff, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.138</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
